[CivilianDisguise X2ArmorTemplate]
FriendlyName="Civilian Disguise"
FriendlyNamePlural="Civilian Disguises"
BriefSummary="These suits of civilian clothing can serve as disguises for our operatives in the field. They will make our soldiers harder for ADVENT to detect, but provide no protection whatsoever."
TacticalText="<Bullet/> The Civilian Disguise makes a soldier harder to detect by enemy forces and shortens infiltration time.\n<Bullet/> However, this disguise is paper thin. Soldiers wearing it should avoid heavy engagements if possible, using their enhanced mobility and stealth."

[AdventDisguise X2ArmorTemplate]
FriendlyName="ADVENT Disguise"
FriendlyNamePlural="ADVENT Disguises"
BriefSummary="The data gleaned from ADVENT's neural implants allows us to pass soldiers off as ADVENT troopers. Surveillance systems will be utterly fooled thanks to the neural transponder, but actual enemies may be less convinced."
TacticalText="<Bullet/> The ADVENT Disguise makes a soldier much harder to detect by enemy forces and shortens infiltration time.\n<Bullet/> The transponders of this disguise render the user invisible to ADVENT security towers.\n<Bullet/> The mixture of alien alloy and steel used by ADVENT provides increased protection over civilian disguises, but no mobility bonus."

[HolographicDisguise X2ArmorTemplate]
FriendlyName="Holographic Disguise"
FriendlyNamePlural="Holographic Disguises"
BriefSummary="Utilizing advanced holographic technology, this new disguise will provide unmatched stealth capability to our operatives without compromising on survivability or mobility."
TacticalText="<Bullet/> The Holographic Disguise makes a soldier nearly impossible to detect by enemy forces and shortens infiltration time.\n<Bullet/> This disguise also contains ADVENT transponders, allowing the soldier passage underneath ADVENT security towers.\n<Bullet/> The nanoweave outer shell of the Holographic disguise grants protection superior to the ADVENT disguise, while retaining the mobility of the Civilian Disguise."

[HoloProjector X2EquipmentTemplate]
FriendlyName="Holoprojector"
FriendlyNamePlural="Holoprojectors"
BriefSummary="Derived from the Faceless biology, the Holoprojector generates a holographic sheath for the soldier's weapon, reducing its impact on covertness."
TacticalText="<Bullet/> The Holoprojector reduces the impact of the soldier's primary weapon on infiltration time." 

[AdaptiveCamo X2EquipmentTemplate]
FriendlyName="Adaptive Camo"
FriendlyNamePlural="Adaptive Camo"
BriefSummary="Based on patterns observed in the Spectre, the Adaptive Camo can be applied to armor to actively reflect enemy security sweeps, reducing the suit's impact on covertness."
TacticalText="<Bullet/> Adaptive Camo reduces the impact of the soldier's armor on infiltration time." 

[TLE_KevlarArmor X2ArmorTemplate]
FriendlyName="Scavenged Field Armor"
FriendlyNamePlural="Scavenged Field Armor"
BriefSummary="This basic armor consists of improvised protection cobbled together from salvage and Resistance arms caches. It provides minimal protection against ADVENT and alien weaponry."
TacticalText="<Bullet/> All soldiers receive Kevlar Armor as part of their basic kit.\n<Bullet/> Research can give us access to better armor."

[TLE_PlatedArmor X2ArmorTemplate]
FriendlyName="Prototype Field Plate"
FriendlyNamePlural="Prototype Field Plate"
BriefSummary="Using scavenged plates of ADVENT armor, this suit provides increased protection and additional inventory capacity for our soldiers."
TacticalText="<Bullet/> Mid-weight armor based on ADVENT salvage.\n<Bullet/> As a medium-class armor, it provides a slot for one additional inventory item."

[TLE_PoweredArmor X2ArmorTemplate]
FriendlyName="Experimental Power Armor"
FriendlyNamePlural="Experimental Power Armor"
BriefSummary="Our new mastery of the alien's Elerium technology has lead us to the ultimate in battle armor. Elerium powered armor provides unprecedented survivability and versatility in the battle against increasingly powerful alien enemies."
TacticalText="<Bullet/> Top tier medium-class armor available.\n<Bullet/> Power Armor has 2 inventory item slots."

